 forms of knowing, socio-economic and political coping tactics, conceptions of history, and faith-based traditions circulate within and between sacred spaces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAnthropology of religionzMexico. 0aGuadalupe, Our Lady ofxCult. 0aSacred spacezMexico. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  abible.  acatholic church.  acatholicism.  achicago.  achicano.  achristianity.  acultural anthropology.  ades plaines.  adevotional labor.  adoctrine.  afaith.  afestivals.  agender.  ahispanic american.  ahispanic.  aimmigration.  alatino.  alatinx.  amexican nationals.  amexico city.  anonfiction.  aperformance.  apiety.  apilgrimage.  apopular religion.  aprayers.  areligion.  areligious performance.  areligious tradition.  areligious.  asacred spaces.  asaints.  ashrine.  asidewalk shrine.  aspirituality.  atepeyac.  atheology.  aurban planning.  avirgin of guadalupe.  aworship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026833340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094880840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948808/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY